  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Peel the <strong>butternut squash</strong> and cut in half lengthways using a sharp knife, then remove the seeds with a spoon and cut the <strong>butternut squash</strong> into 1 cm cubes</p>\n<p>Peel the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>diced butternut squash</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the <strong>butternut squash</strong> has softened and is beginning to brown slightly</p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">While the butternut squash roasts, boil a full kettle </span></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>sage</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\n<p>Set aside for later</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Add the <strong>basa fillets</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!) and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></span></p>\n<p>Spread the <strong>horseradish cream</strong> over the <strong>basa fillets</strong>, then top with the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: Press the breadcrumbs firmly into the fish to get them to stick!</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the fish is golden and cooked through</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the fish is<strong> </strong>cooking, heat a small pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until softened </p>\n<p>Add 50g <span class=\"text-danger\">[100g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> and cook for 1 min or until melted</p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Add the <strong>chopped sage</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and stir it all together, then remove the pot from the heat – this is your<strong> sage butter</strong></span></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Meanwhile, add the <strong>green beans</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></span></p>\n<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Once cooked, drain the <strong>green beans</strong> and add them to the <strong>sage butter </strong>- these are your <strong>sage-butter green beans</strong></span></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> roasted</strong> <strong>squash </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong> to a pot or large bowl and crush everything up using a fork or masher (it's ok to have lumps!) – this is your <strong>crushed squash</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2332Step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Serve the <strong>crispy horseradish fish</strong> over the<strong> crushed squash</strong> with the <strong>sage-butter green beans</strong> to the side</span></p>\n<p>Drizzle over any remaining <strong>sage butter</strong> </p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
